Dear Hiring Team,

I am writing to express my interest in the *Software Engineer I* role at *Uber*. I bring three years of experience building backend systems, production services, and distributed automation, along with a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University.

At Sperse, I built a *Python* / *FastAPI* multi-agent CRM backend that routes requests across 40+ specialized sub-agents for 10,000+ users, and I designed a *large-scale distributed systems* orchestration layer with *Temporal* and *Redis* to keep workflows durable, resumable, and observable. To keep those systems production-ready, I built a production *MCP* server with *FastMCP* exposing 160+ backend actions, added *debugging and monitoring for production services*, and wired GitHub Actions *CI/CD* *deployment processes* with OpenTelemetry trace-based evals and *Docker* and *Kubernetes* rollouts. That work maps directly to the backend development, APIs, reliability, and engineering productivity needs of this role.

At Qualitest, I designed the technology stack for a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in *Java* and *Spring Boot* with *PostgreSQL* and *Redis*, using *object-oriented design*, *APIs*, and *architecture* patterns to handle file uploads, downloads, and deletions across *Google Cloud Storage*, *S3*, and *MinIO* via expiring signed URLs. I also reduced *SQL* query latency by optimizing *PostgreSQL* with window functions, materialized views, and indexes, and orchestrated long-running jobs with *AWS Step Functions* to reduce *AWS Lambda* timeouts and improve error recovery across *100K+* weekly executions. That experience strengthened my ability to design *scalable and resilient systems*, *collaborate across teams*, and solve *production issues in product and system reliability*.

Uber's mission to reimagine the way the world moves for the better resonates with me because it combines real-world impact with *grit, agility and adaptability*. I would welcome the chance to contribute to the marketplace systems, APIs, and production services that keep Uber moving, and to do so in a culture grounded in flexibility and collaboration. Thank you for your time and consideration; I look forward to discussing how my background aligns with *this team and its mission*.

